snippet.title: Math Definitions : What Is the Definition of an Axis in Math?
snippet.description:
An axis in math is a combination of number lines with positive and negative values that meet at an origin with a zero value. Discover more about the definition of an axis with tips from a mathematics tutor in this free video on math lessons.

Expert: Ken Au
Bio: Ken Au is a math teacher and tutor for middle school through college levels. Au holds several international patents and has published numerous technical papers.
Filmmaker: Mark Bullard
